```

I will update my PR to implement the object solution.
You can also notice that I tested Set and object solution for deep object unicity check and for that check only the Double loop solution is working. I will so implement the deepUniq function with the double loop solution (I made the deep check using lodash for going faster for testing but for final implementation I will make it in an hand made function to avoid adding lodash in Zod dependencies just for that utility.

PS: trying to go further in testing I also noticed that on big arrays with more than 10 000 000 items you can reach Set maximun size limit. The Set solution would then be not suitable for a production reliable librairy like Zod  (even if I do not recommend using the uniq check on such arrays because of processing time expect for exceptional use cases)

